# Skillet Localization

## Pattern

Each locale file registers via AceLocale-2.2:

```lua
local L = AceLibrary("AceLocale-2.2"):new("Skillet")
L:RegisterTranslations("enUS", function() return {
    ["KEY"] = "English text",
} end)
```

Non-enUS locales use translated strings; untranslated keys may use `["KEY"] = true` to fall back to enUS.

## Adding Strings

1. Add English key to `Locale/Locale-enUS.lua` first
2. Add the same key to all other `Locale/Locale-*.lua` files (translate or `true`)
3. Reference in code as `L["KEY"]` — never hardcode user-visible English in Lua outside enUS locale

## Key Naming

Follow existing convention: `SCREAMINGKEY` for simple labels, descriptive phrases for sentences (e.g. `["can be created from reagents in your inventory"]`).

## Options & Waterfall

Option names/descriptions in `Skillet.lua` options table use `L[...]` keys defined in locale files — add both `NAME` and `DESC` variants where existing options do.
